article.description: Takal Molson had 21 points as Canisius narrowly defeated St. Peter's 64-60 on Sunday.
article.headline: Molson scores 21 to carry Canisius past St. Peter's 64-60
article.linkText: Molson scores 21 to carry Canisius past St. Peter's 64-60
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- Takal Molson had 21 points as Canisius narrowly defeated St. Peter's 64-60 on Sunday. Scott Hitchon had 11 points for Canisius (11-13, 8-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Malik Johnson added 11 points and eight assists. Derrick Woods had 14 points for the Peacocks (6-17, 3-8), whose losing streak reached five games. Samuel Idowu added 11 points. Canisius faces Fairfield at home on Friday. St. Peter's takes on Iona on the road on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
